---
description: Create an ITL extension development branch
agent: code
---

Use this command only from the `master` worktree. Treat any text after `/itl-new-extension-branch` as the development branch name. If it is missing, ask for one short value.

Before launching, ask in chat whether the branch should create an `Empty` extension or load an existing `CFE`, then collect the extension name and the CFE path when applicable. If the developer explicitly does not know these values yet, create the branch without extension parameters; its saved `pending` state will make extension setup the mandatory first agent-guided step in the new worktree. Never ask the developer to open a terminal or copy a PowerShell command.

Run the monitored helper launcher from the current project directory so the manual unsafe-action protection confirmation is visible:

If the agent shell tool supports `timeout_ms`, run this lifecycle command with `timeout_ms >= 3900000` by default so the outer shell outlives the 3600-second Designer limit; if that limit is configured higher, raise the outer timeout too. Do not use `120000 ms` or other short defaults because the helper may launch 1C Designer/Enterprise operations.

For an Empty extension:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\.agents\skills\1c-workflow\scripts\run-itl-command.ps1 -Windowed -- -Action new-extension-dev-branch -DevBranchName "<dev-branch-name>" -ExtensionInitMode Empty -ExtensionName "<extension-name>" -OfferOpenAgent
```

For an existing CFE, use the same command with `-ExtensionInitMode Cfe` and `-ExtensionSourcePath "<absolute-file.cfe>"`. If the values are explicitly unknown, omit all three extension parameters but keep `-OfferOpenAgent`.

Use direct `agent-1c.ps1` only for non-interactive automation that explicitly sets `DEV_BRANCH_UNSAFE_ACTION_PROTECTION_SETUP=skip` after the unsafe-action protection is configured separately.

The helper creates the sibling worktree and branch infobase, then runs the transactional extension initialization inside that worktree. On success with a non-empty `userReport`, make the final response exactly that report rendered as Markdown, with no introduction, conclusion, or separate worktree instruction. Do not translate it, convert it to a table, rename or merge fields, reorder or omit lines, summarize it, or replace it with `requiredAction` or a generic success sentence, and do not expose the internal helper command. The helper already includes every setting, MCP/Browser line, instruction, advice, pending extension setup, and window-opening action in Russian. Do not wrap it in a code fence or read `console.log` on success.
